we started a mini-series through this psalm,

00:00:25.940 --> 00:00:27.520
Psalm chapter number three.

00:00:27.520 --> 00:00:30.959
And on the first six verses, we took two verses a week.

00:00:30.959 --> 00:00:33.819
And during those first three lessons,

00:00:33.819 --> 00:00:35.380
as we looked at this psalm,

00:00:35.380 --> 00:00:38.659
we discovered the reality of the situation

00:00:38.659 --> 00:00:39.700
in verses one and two.

00:00:39.700 --> 00:00:40.939
In verses three and four,

00:00:40.939 --> 00:00:45.540
we discovered the response of David to the situation.

00:00:45.540 --> 00:00:47.119
And then in verses five and six,

00:00:47.119 --> 00:00:49.659
we looked at the rest of David

00:00:49.659 --> 00:00:52.139
and how that he rested in the Lord.

00:00:52.139 --> 00:00:53.740
Notice in verse number one, the Bible says,

00:00:53.740 --> 00:00:57.500
"'Lord, how are they increased that trouble me?

00:00:57.500 --> 00:00:59.979
"'Many are they that rise up against me,

00:00:59.979 --> 00:01:02.500
"'many there be which say of my soul,

00:01:02.500 --> 00:01:06.500
"'there is no help for him in God, Selah.'"

00:01:06.500 --> 00:01:10.160
This was the reality of the situation that David was facing.

00:01:10.160 --> 00:01:12.459
We know that the Bible teaches us,

00:01:12.459 --> 00:01:15.419
and as we look at contextually what's going on,

00:01:15.419 --> 00:01:18.239
you look back and you can find that really the setting

00:01:18.239 --> 00:01:22.339
of this particular psalm is believed to be

00:01:22.339 --> 00:01:26.419
that of the revolt, the rebellion and revolt of Absalom.

00:01:26.419 --> 00:01:27.419
And you can read of that

00:01:27.419 --> 00:01:30.620
in 2 Samuel chapters 15 through 19.

00:01:30.620 --> 00:01:32.900
And you see that it was a serious situation.

00:01:32.900 --> 00:01:35.680
David was not exaggerating the circumstances.

00:01:35.680 --> 00:01:40.099
He was not just pretending that this was some difficulty.

00:01:40.099 --> 00:01:43.540
This was a serious situation in which he was dealing with.

00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:46.279
And we noted the reality of the situation.

00:01:46.279 --> 00:01:48.760
We said that the response to the situation

00:01:48.760 --> 00:01:50.940
was noteworthy and exemplary.

00:01:50.940 --> 00:01:52.940
You find it in verses three and four.

00:01:52.940 --> 00:01:56.459
Notice what David says as he responds to the situation,

00:01:56.459 --> 00:02:00.459
"'But thou, O Lord, art a shield for me.'"

00:02:00.459 --> 00:02:01.819
Remember, they were saying

00:02:01.819 --> 00:02:04.980
there is no help for him in God, Selah.

00:02:04.980 --> 00:02:06.699
But David says,

00:02:06.699 --> 00:02:10.779
"'I understand, God, that you are a shield for me,

00:02:10.779 --> 00:02:15.220
"'my glory and the lifter up of mine head.'"

00:02:15.220 --> 00:02:17.220
Notice what he says in verse number four,

00:02:17.220 --> 00:02:19.360
"'I cried unto the Lord with my voice,

00:02:19.360 --> 00:02:23.619
"'and he heard me out of his holy hill, Selah.'"

00:02:23.619 --> 00:02:27.539
Isn't that a great response to such a difficult situation?

00:02:27.539 --> 00:02:29.899
And we find that it's important for us

00:02:29.899 --> 00:02:32.139
to understand the response of David

00:02:32.139 --> 00:02:36.380
and understand that we too should respond in like fashion

00:02:36.380 --> 00:02:38.899
when we deal with difficulty and adversity

00:02:38.899 --> 00:02:42.619
and troubles and trials, how we cry to the Lord,

00:02:42.619 --> 00:02:46.339
how we trust in God and depend upon him.

00:02:46.460 --> 00:02:49.419
And after we pour out our heart to God,

00:02:49.419 --> 00:02:52.460
after we carry our burdens to the Lord,

00:02:52.460 --> 00:02:54.500
knowing that he cares for us,

00:02:54.500 --> 00:02:56.619
we find that we can have a great rest,

00:02:56.619 --> 00:02:59.979
a great peace that passeth all understanding.

00:02:59.979 --> 00:03:02.020
And that's what we see in verses five and six.

00:03:02.020 --> 00:03:02.860
Notice the Bible says,

00:03:02.860 --> 00:03:04.899
"'I laid me down and slept.

00:03:04.899 --> 00:03:07.660
"'I awaked, for the Lord sustained me.

00:03:07.660 --> 00:03:10.300
"'I will not be afraid of 10,000s of people

00:03:10.300 --> 00:03:13.259
"'that have set themselves against me roundabout.'"

00:03:13.259 --> 00:03:14.100
Why?

00:03:14.100 --> 00:03:16.619
Because he's trusting in the Lord

00:03:16.619 --> 00:03:20.820
and he's taken his burden to the Lord and he's laid it.

00:03:20.820 --> 00:03:23.460
The Bible tells us, "'Cast thy burden upon the Lord.

00:03:23.460 --> 00:03:25.860
"'He will sustain thee.'"

00:03:25.860 --> 00:03:28.660
Knowing that we're to cast all of our care upon him.

00:03:28.660 --> 00:03:29.500
Why?

00:03:29.500 --> 00:03:31.899
"'For he careth for us, he careth for you.'"

00:03:31.899 --> 00:03:33.500
And what great truth that is.

00:03:33.500 --> 00:03:35.660
And we find here in verses five and six,

00:03:35.660 --> 00:03:40.100
this great peace and this rest that David experiences.

00:03:40.100 --> 00:03:41.740
And how in our lives,

00:03:41.740 --> 00:03:44.580
when we deal with troubles and trials and difficulties,

00:03:44.580 --> 00:03:47.339
we respond to those by going to God

00:03:47.339 --> 00:03:51.179
and then we can rest knowing that God is able.

00:03:51.179 --> 00:03:52.860
And what great truth that is

00:03:52.860 --> 00:03:55.820
and how important it is that we understand

00:03:55.820 --> 00:03:58.020
that rest that is possible for us.

