00:08:58.380 --> 00:09:01.820
of our study this evening confirms for us two truths

00:09:01.820 --> 00:09:04.500
that we find throughout the entirety of the Psalm.

00:09:04.500 --> 00:09:06.900
Notice the first phrase here in verse number seven.

00:09:06.900 --> 00:09:11.900
Arise, O Lord, save me, O my God.

00:09:12.700 --> 00:09:14.780
I believe that in this statement

00:09:14.780 --> 00:09:18.900
that the two truths that are confirmed to us are this,

00:09:19.900 --> 00:09:23.219
number one, David is confident in the Lord.

00:09:24.219 --> 00:09:27.179
He is confident in the ability of God

00:09:27.179 --> 00:09:29.739
and the power of the Lord to save him.

00:09:29.739 --> 00:09:31.260
He is confident.

00:09:31.260 --> 00:09:35.140
He is convinced that God is able,

00:09:35.140 --> 00:09:37.059
and I believe he has that full confidence.

00:09:37.059 --> 00:09:40.739
And we need to have confidence in God as we live life,

00:09:40.739 --> 00:09:43.020
as we go through this journey,

00:09:43.020 --> 00:09:46.500
as we deal with difficulties and adversities,

00:09:46.500 --> 00:09:48.700
that we can have confidence in knowing

00:09:49.380 --> 00:09:50.380
that our God is able,

00:09:50.380 --> 00:09:52.179
that there's nothing that's too hard for him,

00:09:52.179 --> 00:09:54.619
that there's no trial, no situation,

00:09:54.619 --> 00:09:57.340
no circumstance that's beyond his ability,

00:09:57.340 --> 00:10:00.020
and we need to understand that we.

00:10:00.020 --> 00:10:01.660
are to be confident in him.

00:10:01.660 --> 00:10:04.200
I believe the second truth that is revealed to us

00:10:04.200 --> 00:10:06.540
in this statement to begin verse number seven

00:10:06.540 --> 00:10:09.760
is that David is dependent upon the Lord.

00:10:09.760 --> 00:10:14.260
Notice he says, arise, O Lord, save me, O my God.

00:10:14.260 --> 00:10:16.700
The personal relationship is there, obviously.

00:10:16.700 --> 00:10:19.640
He says, O my God, the personal understanding.

00:10:19.640 --> 00:10:22.260
But you find that he's dependent upon the Lord.

00:10:22.260 --> 00:10:26.560
He's trusting that God, he is confident in God's ability,

00:10:26.560 --> 00:10:29.380
but he's fully dependent on God to work.

00:10:29.460 --> 00:10:31.380
And how we need to depend upon God,

00:10:31.380 --> 00:10:33.740
trust in him wholly and completely,

00:10:33.740 --> 00:10:36.300
and you find that he is wholly true.

00:10:36.300 --> 00:10:39.860
And he is trustworthy, and we ought to rejoice in that.

