And I find that David is rejoicing here,

00:12:26.900 --> 00:12:30.980
and he's rejoicing because God has worked.

00:12:30.980 --> 00:12:34.820
Not only should the recollection of God's working

00:12:34.820 --> 00:12:38.060
and the remembrance that is mentioned here for,

00:12:38.060 --> 00:12:40.980
he's speaking of those past victories

00:12:40.980 --> 00:12:43.140
and the past working of God,

00:12:43.140 --> 00:12:45.140
not only should that cause us to rejoice,

00:12:45.140 --> 00:12:47.320
but I believe this evening that it should cause us

00:12:47.320 --> 00:12:50.780
to trust God in our current situation.

00:12:52.080 --> 00:12:53.200
Think about the rehearsing.

00:12:53.200 --> 00:12:54.760
Think about what he's remembering.

00:12:54.760 --> 00:12:57.280
It's just summarized in two statements.

00:12:57.280 --> 00:13:00.320
Thou hast smitten all mine enemies upon the cheekbone.

00:13:00.320 --> 00:13:03.280
Thou hast broken the teeth of the ungodly.

00:13:03.280 --> 00:13:06.960
But as David is the one that is penning this psalm,

00:13:06.960 --> 00:13:09.280
as he's recalling and remembering,

00:13:09.280 --> 00:13:11.420
you think about the floods of memories

00:13:11.420 --> 00:13:15.400
that would permeate his mind as he's writing these words,

00:13:15.400 --> 00:13:18.160
and he's mindful of what God has done,

00:13:18.160 --> 00:13:21.400
which will result in the rejoicing,

00:13:21.440 --> 00:13:24.320
but it also leads to trusting,

00:13:24.320 --> 00:13:27.000
because if God was able to do it before,

00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:29.040
then he's able to do it now, right?

00:13:29.040 --> 00:13:30.040
God doesn't change.

00:13:30.040 --> 00:13:32.440
He's the same yesterday and today and forever,

00:13:32.440 --> 00:13:36.360
and we find here that David is rejoicing,

00:13:36.360 --> 00:13:40.300
but through the rejoicing as he set his mind,

00:13:40.300 --> 00:13:43.520
remember I said this, we must purpose to rejoice.

00:13:43.520 --> 00:13:45.440
This is the day the Lord hath made.

00:13:45.440 --> 00:13:48.280
We will rejoice and be glad in it.

00:13:48.280 --> 00:13:50.760
Rejoice in the Lord always,

00:13:51.160 --> 00:13:54.280
and again I say rejoice, rejoice evermore.

00:13:54.280 --> 00:13:57.880
When I purpose to rejoice, all of a sudden,

00:13:57.880 --> 00:14:01.720
what's happening is my focus and my attention is Godward,

00:14:03.320 --> 00:14:07.180
instead of on my problem, instead of on my situation,

00:14:07.180 --> 00:14:09.280
and what we find is that God is greater

00:14:09.280 --> 00:14:12.060
than any situation that we face.

00:14:12.060 --> 00:14:14.160
What happens so often in our lives

00:14:14.160 --> 00:14:16.720
is that we have so much of our focus

00:14:16.720 --> 00:14:19.440
and so much of our attention upon our problem,

00:14:19.440 --> 00:14:23.640
and our problem just continues to grow and grow and grow,

00:14:23.640 --> 00:14:27.200
and we're just so focused upon our problem

00:14:27.200 --> 00:14:30.840
that we're not rejoicing as we see David doing here,

00:14:30.840 --> 00:14:33.240
and therefore our attention is not Godward.

00:14:33.240 --> 00:14:36.620
We're just so focused on whatever the problem at hand is.

00:14:37.640 --> 00:14:41.240
We mentioned that in the response in verses three and four

00:14:41.240 --> 00:14:44.840
when he responded by praising the Lord,

00:14:44.840 --> 00:14:47.080
thanking God for who he is,

00:14:47.080 --> 00:14:49.720
and declaring his dependence upon God

00:14:49.720 --> 00:14:51.120
in verses three and four,

00:14:51.120 --> 00:14:54.360
and as we noted that in that study a few weeks ago,

00:14:54.360 --> 00:14:57.080
we understood that that too is how we should respond,

00:14:57.080 --> 00:14:59.560
and when we respond in that fashion,

00:14:59.560 --> 00:15:01.600
our attention is upon the Lord.

00:15:04.240 --> 00:15:06.040
The more we focus on a problem,

00:15:06.040 --> 00:15:08.280
the bigger the problem becomes.

00:15:08.280 --> 00:15:10.940
It just can consume us,

00:15:12.080 --> 00:15:14.880
and we find here that his attention is Godward.

00:15:14.880 --> 00:15:15.720
Why?

00:15:15.720 --> 00:15:17.120
Because he's rejoicing,

00:15:17.120 --> 00:15:20.280
because he's praising God for what he, God,

00:15:20.280 --> 00:15:22.800
has done on his behalf.

00:15:22.800 --> 00:15:26.540
Notice in verse number eight that David recognizes

00:15:26.540 --> 00:15:29.800
that salvation belongeth unto the Lord.

00:15:29.800 --> 00:15:32.880
This here, as you often find in the Old Testament,

00:15:32.880 --> 00:15:34.040
especially in the Book of Psalms,

00:15:34.040 --> 00:15:37.240
the term salvation is not the same use of the word

00:15:37.240 --> 00:15:39.600
that we would use in New Testament Christianity

00:15:39.600 --> 00:15:42.160
of being saved, being born again,

00:15:42.160 --> 00:15:44.220
but it's a word that is often used

00:15:44.560 --> 00:15:46.340
to simply deal with deliverance.

00:15:46.340 --> 00:15:49.740
Now, we understand when we speak of our salvation

00:15:49.740 --> 00:15:51.380
that we're speaking about our deliverance

00:15:51.380 --> 00:15:53.540
from the penalty of sin,

00:15:53.540 --> 00:15:56.940
and here, in many other areas in the Book of Psalms,

00:15:56.940 --> 00:16:00.500
when you read the salvation that is being discussed,

00:16:00.500 --> 00:16:03.420
he's speaking about the deliverance that God has provided,

00:16:03.420 --> 00:16:06.460
such as what he has mentioned in verse number seven,

00:16:06.460 --> 00:16:09.060
where God had smitten all his enemies

00:16:09.060 --> 00:16:11.500
and broken the teeth of the ungodly,

00:16:11.500 --> 00:16:13.640
and notice the recognition here.

00:16:13.640 --> 00:16:16.120
The very truth of this recognition

00:16:16.120 --> 00:16:19.340
that salvation or deliverance belongs to God

00:16:19.340 --> 00:16:21.060
would cause us to rejoice.

00:16:22.100 --> 00:16:24.760
It's not in my power, it's not in my ability

00:16:24.760 --> 00:16:25.880
to provide deliverance.

00:16:25.880 --> 00:16:30.440
It's not up to me to come up with the plan for deliverance.

00:16:30.440 --> 00:16:32.120
You think about the life of David,

00:16:32.120 --> 00:16:34.700
and you think about the many victories,

00:16:34.700 --> 00:16:37.640
the triumphs of David as you read throughout his life.

00:16:37.640 --> 00:16:40.080
Remember, this is near the end of his life.

00:16:40.080 --> 00:16:42.640
This is during the time of the rebellion

00:16:42.640 --> 00:16:43.960
and revolt of Absalom,

00:16:43.960 --> 00:16:46.600
and you think about all that has taken place

00:16:46.600 --> 00:16:48.520
prior to that in the life of David,

00:16:48.520 --> 00:16:52.360
and you read of all of his triumphs and all of the victories,

00:16:52.360 --> 00:16:55.200
and as you begin to fill your mind

00:16:55.200 --> 00:16:57.200
with recalling those great things

00:16:57.200 --> 00:16:59.680
that are recorded in 1 and 2 Samuel,

00:16:59.680 --> 00:17:02.380
and reading of all of those great victories,

00:17:02.380 --> 00:17:05.360
you find that David, as he makes the statement,

00:17:05.360 --> 00:17:07.600
salvation belongeth unto the Lord,

00:17:07.600 --> 00:17:12.160
that just the recognition of that truth

00:17:12.160 --> 00:17:14.520
would lead to rejoicing,

00:17:14.520 --> 00:17:17.880
thanking God that he is our deliverer,

00:17:17.880 --> 00:17:21.420
that he is the one that provides deliverance.

00:17:21.420 --> 00:17:25.880
David fought many times against the Philistines,

00:17:25.880 --> 00:17:29.040
and it started, of course, we understand,

00:17:29.040 --> 00:17:31.180
in that great battle against Goliath,

00:17:31.180 --> 00:17:34.440
and we're familiar with 1 Samuel in chapter number 17,

00:17:34.440 --> 00:17:36.400
and we look at that passage of Scripture,

00:17:36.400 --> 00:17:40.420
and it's a very prominent portion of Scripture,

00:17:40.420 --> 00:17:45.060
and one in which we find just great encouragement,

00:17:45.060 --> 00:17:47.220
and the reality is that when David goes

00:17:47.220 --> 00:17:48.500
to fight against Goliath,

00:17:48.500 --> 00:17:51.120
he was not depending upon himself.

00:17:51.120 --> 00:17:54.760
When Saul tries to give him the armor

00:17:54.760 --> 00:17:56.420
and all that he tries to give him,

00:17:56.420 --> 00:17:59.000
David understands that, listen,

00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:00.900
salvation belongeth unto the Lord.

00:18:00.900 --> 00:18:02.340
He understood that it was God

00:18:02.340 --> 00:18:04.780
that had delivered him previously,

00:18:04.780 --> 00:18:07.680
and that it was God that would fight on his behalf.

00:18:08.520 --> 00:18:10.920
There were times in which he fought the Philistines,

00:18:10.920 --> 00:18:13.520
and there were times in which the Philistines

00:18:13.520 --> 00:18:18.160
invaded cities, and David would seek the face of God.

00:18:18.160 --> 00:18:21.080
He would inquire of the Lord to find out,

00:18:21.080 --> 00:18:23.340
what shall I do, how should I proceed?

00:18:23.340 --> 00:18:26.640
And God would answer, and God would provide direction,

00:18:26.640 --> 00:18:29.200
and as he was depending upon the Lord,

00:18:29.200 --> 00:18:30.920
he understood that it was the Lord

00:18:30.920 --> 00:18:32.840
that brought the deliverance.

00:18:32.840 --> 00:18:35.080
Salvation belongeth unto the Lord.

00:18:35.960 --> 00:18:39.360
Often in our lives, we begin to think about

00:18:39.360 --> 00:18:42.000
these great truths like what we find

00:18:42.000 --> 00:18:44.760
declared here in verse number seven and eight,

00:18:44.760 --> 00:18:47.220
how that we would take those truths

00:18:47.220 --> 00:18:52.000
and allow those to be a catalyst to our rejoicing.

00:18:52.880 --> 00:18:56.000
When you think about the importance of rejoicing

00:18:56.000 --> 00:18:57.800
in the life of a believer,

00:18:57.800 --> 00:19:00.920
and the prominence of rejoicing in our lives,

00:19:00.920 --> 00:19:04.220
and that the Lord is worthy of our praise,

00:19:04.220 --> 00:19:07.860
then there's some statements, some truths such as this

00:19:07.860 --> 00:19:10.040
that will be utilized in our lives

00:19:10.040 --> 00:19:13.400
as a catalyst to cause us to rejoice.

00:19:13.400 --> 00:19:15.739
Salvation belongeth unto the Lord,

00:19:15.739 --> 00:19:17.940
and we just begin to think about the deliverance

00:19:17.940 --> 00:19:20.420
that he's provided for us as New Testament believers

00:19:20.420 --> 00:19:24.460
as we use that term salvation to speak about our redemption.

00:19:24.460 --> 00:19:27.619
Oh man, how that brings a whole nother dynamic

00:19:27.619 --> 00:19:29.679
to the equation and understanding

00:19:29.679 --> 00:19:31.820
that redemption is only through the blood

00:19:31.820 --> 00:19:33.100
of the Lord Jesus Christ,

00:19:33.100 --> 00:19:36.179
and how that ought to cause us to rejoice.

00:19:36.179 --> 00:19:40.500
I couldn't save myself and you can't save yourself, right?

00:19:40.500 --> 00:19:41.820
It's impossible.

00:19:41.820 --> 00:19:45.220
And so we understand even as we would take that term

00:19:45.220 --> 00:19:48.260
and utilize it and apply it the way that we would

00:19:48.260 --> 00:19:49.520
as New Testament believers,

00:19:49.520 --> 00:19:51.540
we can rejoice in understanding

00:19:51.540 --> 00:19:54.300
that salvation belongeth unto the Lord.

00:19:54.300 --> 00:19:56.780
And I'm thankful that he's a wonderful savior.

00:19:57.780 --> 00:20:00.220
Notice the last statement of verse number eight.

00:20:00.220 --> 00:20:07.260
Okay, thy blessing is upon thy people.

00:20:07.260 --> 00:20:08.920
Selah.

00:20:08.920 --> 00:20:10.620
To finish out the psalm,

00:20:10.620 --> 00:20:12.480
we find that David references

00:20:12.480 --> 00:20:14.340
the blessing of God.

00:20:14.340 --> 00:20:16.080
You think about the blessing of God.

00:20:16.080 --> 00:20:19.300
I'm so thankful for God's good hand of blessing.

00:20:19.300 --> 00:20:21.340
I'm thankful for the many blessings

00:20:21.340 --> 00:20:23.120
that He's bestowed upon us.

00:20:23.120 --> 00:20:25.760
We sing songs about count your blessings,

00:20:25.760 --> 00:20:28.000
name them one by one.

00:20:28.000 --> 00:20:30.800
We understand that as we would consider

00:20:30.800 --> 00:20:33.420
thy blessing is upon thy people,

00:20:33.420 --> 00:20:35.760
again, a reason to rejoice

00:20:35.760 --> 00:20:37.220
in the rejoicing of David,

00:20:37.220 --> 00:20:38.760
a catalyst if you will,

00:20:38.760 --> 00:20:41.040
just as we saw in that first statement

00:20:41.040 --> 00:20:42.160
of verse 8,

00:20:42.160 --> 00:20:44.320
to lead us, to lead David

00:20:44.320 --> 00:20:47.080
to a place of rejoicing.

00:20:47.080 --> 00:20:48.320
And I want you to understand

00:20:48.320 --> 00:20:50.280
that as David is remembering

00:20:50.280 --> 00:20:53.840
the fact that God is blessing

00:20:53.840 --> 00:20:57.040
and that His blessing is upon His people,

00:20:57.040 --> 00:20:58.820
we must be mindful of this truth

00:20:58.820 --> 00:21:00.660
this evening that God's blessings

00:21:00.660 --> 00:21:03.200
come in different forms

00:21:03.200 --> 00:21:06.000
and at different times.

00:21:06.000 --> 00:21:07.280
There can be something in our life

00:21:07.280 --> 00:21:08.880
that's a blessing and sometimes

00:21:08.880 --> 00:21:09.880
we don't really look at it

00:21:09.880 --> 00:21:11.280
as being a blessing

00:21:11.280 --> 00:21:13.840
because we just have a wrong perspective

00:21:13.840 --> 00:21:16.800
because we think that a blessing

00:21:16.800 --> 00:21:19.180
is something that is defined

00:21:19.180 --> 00:21:23.280
by our finite ability to describe

00:21:23.280 --> 00:21:25.680
or to define what a blessing is,

00:21:25.680 --> 00:21:27.000
but the reality is that

00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:29.280
in God's infinite wisdom

00:21:29.280 --> 00:21:30.560
and in His mercy,

00:21:30.560 --> 00:21:33.000
He gives blessings to His people

00:21:33.000 --> 00:21:34.160
and there are times in which

00:21:34.160 --> 00:21:35.960
we may not even recognize things

00:21:35.960 --> 00:21:38.400
as being blessings.

