00:24:58.320 --> 00:25:00.400
and he now rests.

00:25:00.400 --> 00:25:01.640
And the Bible tells us

00:25:01.640 --> 00:25:03.960
that he's rejoicing.

00:25:03.960 --> 00:25:04.720
It's interesting,

00:25:04.720 --> 00:25:06.080
as you note the truth,

00:25:06.080 --> 00:25:07.240
if you want to take a moment

00:25:07.240 --> 00:25:09.040
and turn to the book of Philippians

00:25:09.040 --> 00:25:10.200
and the fourth chapter,

00:25:10.200 --> 00:25:11.240
we've mentioned already

00:25:11.240 --> 00:25:12.480
verse number four

00:25:12.480 --> 00:25:13.600
by way of introduction,

00:25:13.600 --> 00:25:14.960
rejoice in the Lord always.

00:25:14.960 --> 00:25:17.320
And again, I say rejoice.

00:25:17.320 --> 00:25:19.000
A few verses later,

00:25:19.000 --> 00:25:21.000
we find the Bible tells us

00:25:22.160 --> 00:25:24.120
this truth about being careful

00:25:24.120 --> 00:25:25.880
for nothing in Philippians

00:25:25.880 --> 00:25:27.000
four and verse number six.

00:25:27.000 --> 00:25:28.040
Be careful for nothing.

00:25:28.040 --> 00:25:29.880
But in everything,

00:25:29.880 --> 00:25:31.880
by prayer and supplication

00:25:31.880 --> 00:25:33.840
with thanksgiving,

00:25:33.840 --> 00:25:34.760
let your requests

00:25:34.760 --> 00:25:36.000
be made known unto God,

00:25:36.000 --> 00:25:37.760
it says, and the peace of God,

00:25:37.760 --> 00:25:39.800
which passeth all understanding

00:25:39.800 --> 00:25:41.080
shall keep your hearts

00:25:41.080 --> 00:25:43.200
and minds through Christ Jesus.

00:25:44.440 --> 00:25:46.040
Paul goes on to say

00:25:46.040 --> 00:25:46.880
in verse number 10,

00:25:46.880 --> 00:25:48.640
but I rejoiced in the Lord

00:25:48.640 --> 00:25:51.040
greatly that now at the last

00:25:51.040 --> 00:25:51.760
your care of me

00:25:51.760 --> 00:25:52.920
hath flourished again,

00:25:52.920 --> 00:25:54.360
wherein you were also careful,

00:25:54.360 --> 00:25:56.080
but you lacked opportunity.

00:25:56.080 --> 00:25:57.000
Not that I speak

00:25:57.000 --> 00:25:57.920
in respect of want,

00:25:57.920 --> 00:25:58.720
for I have learned

00:25:58.720 --> 00:25:59.560
in what sort of state

00:25:59.560 --> 00:26:01.880
I am there with to be content,

00:26:01.880 --> 00:26:04.200
understanding that God's purposes

00:26:04.720 --> 00:26:06.320
in his in his life

00:26:06.320 --> 00:26:08.600
are for a purpose and for a reason

00:26:08.840 --> 00:26:10.400
and therefore his good.

00:26:10.400 --> 00:26:11.200
But you notice,

00:26:11.200 --> 00:26:12.280
as you look at verses

00:26:12.280 --> 00:26:13.680
four through seven

00:26:13.680 --> 00:26:14.880
and you compare that

00:26:14.880 --> 00:26:16.440
with the truth of Psalm three

00:26:16.440 --> 00:26:17.400
that we've studied here

00:26:17.400 --> 00:26:18.360
for four weeks now

00:26:18.360 --> 00:26:19.720
on Wednesday evening

00:26:19.720 --> 00:26:21.320
and you see the rejoicing,

00:26:21.320 --> 00:26:23.160
it's kind of reverse order,

00:26:23.160 --> 00:26:24.480
but you see the rejoicing

00:26:24.480 --> 00:26:25.440
in the Lord always.

00:26:25.440 --> 00:26:26.760
And again, I say rejoice.

00:26:26.760 --> 00:26:28.640
We see that in verses seven

00:26:28.640 --> 00:26:30.440
and eight of Psalm three.

00:26:30.440 --> 00:26:31.360
You find that he says,

00:26:31.360 --> 00:26:32.400
be careful for nothing,

00:26:32.400 --> 00:26:33.640
but in everything by prayer

00:26:33.640 --> 00:26:34.520
and supplication

00:26:34.520 --> 00:26:35.760
with thanksgiving,

00:26:35.760 --> 00:26:36.720
let your requests

00:26:36.720 --> 00:26:37.880
be made known unto God.

00:26:37.880 --> 00:26:39.160
And really in Psalm three,

00:26:39.160 --> 00:26:40.320
you see that in verses

00:26:40.320 --> 00:26:41.840
three and four.

00:26:41.840 --> 00:26:42.920
The peace of God

00:26:42.920 --> 00:26:43.640
that is mentioned

00:26:43.640 --> 00:26:44.640
in verse number seven

00:26:44.640 --> 00:26:45.920
of Philippians four

00:26:45.920 --> 00:26:47.320
is what we see in verses

00:26:47.320 --> 00:26:49.440
five and six of Psalm three,

00:26:50.040 --> 00:26:51.680
where there's that great peace,

00:26:51.680 --> 00:26:53.920
the rest that David experiences.

00:26:54.160 --> 00:26:54.920
And then, of course,

00:26:54.920 --> 00:26:55.680
the situation

00:26:55.680 --> 00:26:56.640
or the circumstance,

00:26:56.640 --> 00:26:57.600
really, you'd have to look

00:26:57.600 --> 00:26:58.840
at the entirety

00:26:58.840 --> 00:27:00.080
of the book of Philippians

00:27:00.080 --> 00:27:02.040
to understand that Paul is writing

00:27:02.040 --> 00:27:04.080
from a place of Roman prison.

00:27:05.120 --> 00:27:05.920
And Paul's writing

00:27:05.920 --> 00:27:08.200
from a place of Roman prison,

00:27:08.200 --> 00:27:10.120
but he's rejoicing.

00:27:10.120 --> 00:27:11.560
It's a book that really

00:27:11.560 --> 00:27:12.640
the theme of the book

00:27:12.640 --> 00:27:13.360
of Philippians

00:27:13.360 --> 00:27:16.600
is the joy of the Lord and rejoice.

00:27:17.160 --> 00:27:19.200
And Paul's writing from prison.

00:27:19.200 --> 00:27:21.800
He's saying rejoice.

00:27:22.320 --> 00:27:24.720
In fact, it's in my mind,

00:27:24.720 --> 00:27:26.840
it's so connected

00:27:26.840 --> 00:27:28.320
when you think about the theme

00:27:28.320 --> 00:27:29.800
of the book of Philippians

00:27:29.800 --> 00:27:32.560
and the repeated reference

00:27:32.560 --> 00:27:34.040
to rejoicing,

00:27:34.040 --> 00:27:35.080
because you'll recall

00:27:35.080 --> 00:27:36.720
that while Paul and Silas

00:27:36.720 --> 00:27:38.520
were in prison

00:27:38.520 --> 00:27:39.840
after they'd been beaten

00:27:39.840 --> 00:27:41.640
and cast in the inner prison,

00:27:41.640 --> 00:27:42.320
it was there

00:27:42.320 --> 00:27:44.240
that they were rejoicing.

00:27:45.240 --> 00:27:47.000
They're praying and singing

00:27:47.000 --> 00:27:48.640
praise unto the Lord.

00:27:48.640 --> 00:27:50.160
They're rejoicing.

00:27:50.160 --> 00:27:50.880
God worked.

00:27:50.880 --> 00:27:52.560
God moved the earthquake.

00:27:52.560 --> 00:27:53.760
And we, of course,

00:27:53.760 --> 00:27:55.200
are familiar with the response

00:27:55.200 --> 00:27:57.000
of the Philippian jailer.

00:27:57.000 --> 00:27:59.920
Sirs, what must I do to be saved?

00:28:01.040 --> 00:28:04.480
In that adverse situation,

00:28:04.480 --> 00:28:05.480
the circumstance

00:28:05.480 --> 00:28:07.080
that Paul and Silas

00:28:07.080 --> 00:28:07.920
could have been in there

00:28:07.920 --> 00:28:09.240
saying this isn't fair,

00:28:09.240 --> 00:28:11.160
they've falsely accused us

00:28:11.160 --> 00:28:12.280
and they've beaten us

00:28:12.280 --> 00:28:13.880
and so on and so forth.

00:28:14.080 --> 00:28:15.280
And I just can't believe

00:28:15.280 --> 00:28:16.160
we're in this place.

00:28:16.160 --> 00:28:18.320
We're just trying to serve God.

00:28:18.320 --> 00:28:19.160
All we're trying to do

00:28:19.160 --> 00:28:20.000
is obey God

00:28:20.000 --> 00:28:21.120
and look at what's happened.

00:28:21.120 --> 00:28:23.520
Look at what it's got us.

00:28:23.520 --> 00:28:24.840
Do you think the Philippian jailer

00:28:24.840 --> 00:28:25.560
would say, sirs,

00:28:25.560 --> 00:28:28.120
what must I do to be saved?

00:28:28.120 --> 00:28:29.440
I have a hard time believing

00:28:29.440 --> 00:28:32.000
that they would respond that way.

00:28:32.920 --> 00:28:34.280
But when they hear,

00:28:34.280 --> 00:28:36.400
when he hears men

00:28:36.400 --> 00:28:38.560
that are praising God

00:28:38.560 --> 00:28:40.880
after being beaten.

00:28:41.000 --> 00:28:42.040
That are rejoicing

00:28:42.040 --> 00:28:44.680
and singing and praying.

00:28:44.680 --> 00:28:47.160
Man, that's impactful.

00:28:47.160 --> 00:28:48.960
This evening, as we conclude

00:28:48.960 --> 00:28:51.280
our mini series on Psalm three,

00:28:52.200 --> 00:28:55.000
I hope that we've been encouraged.

00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:55.920
We've understood

00:28:55.920 --> 00:28:57.960
that we can relate to the psalmist

00:28:57.960 --> 00:29:00.000
and so many other portions

00:29:00.000 --> 00:29:00.720
of Scripture

00:29:00.720 --> 00:29:02.320
throughout the word of God

00:29:02.320 --> 00:29:03.680
that is relatable to us

00:29:03.680 --> 00:29:04.560
as human beings,

00:29:04.560 --> 00:29:06.560
that David was a man.

00:29:06.560 --> 00:29:08.360
He was a human being just as we are,

00:29:08.360 --> 00:29:09.760
and he dealt with difficulties

00:29:09.760 --> 00:29:10.600
and adversities.

00:29:10.600 --> 00:29:11.800
And when we think about

00:29:11.800 --> 00:29:13.440
the reality of the situation

00:29:13.440 --> 00:29:14.800
and the pressures of life

00:29:14.800 --> 00:29:16.320
and the oppositions

00:29:16.320 --> 00:29:18.240
that we deal with,

00:29:18.240 --> 00:29:20.960
how do we respond to those?

00:29:20.960 --> 00:29:22.360
We must respond the way

00:29:22.360 --> 00:29:23.680
that David did in verses

00:29:23.680 --> 00:29:24.880
three and four.

00:29:24.880 --> 00:29:25.880
We must respond

00:29:25.880 --> 00:29:27.120
by reminding ourselves

00:29:27.120 --> 00:29:29.080
who our God is to us.

00:29:29.080 --> 00:29:30.560
He's my shield,

00:29:30.560 --> 00:29:33.360
my protector, my defender.

00:29:33.360 --> 00:29:34.840
He's my glory.

00:29:34.840 --> 00:29:37.520
He's the lifter up of my head.

00:29:37.520 --> 00:29:38.840
When the when the world

00:29:38.840 --> 00:29:40.080
seems to be against us

00:29:40.080 --> 00:29:41.560
and we can find ourselves

00:29:41.560 --> 00:29:42.760
becoming discouraged,

00:29:42.760 --> 00:29:43.480
and I mentioned this

00:29:43.480 --> 00:29:43.960
when we looked at

00:29:43.960 --> 00:29:45.200
that second lesson,

00:29:45.200 --> 00:29:46.120
there are times in which

00:29:46.120 --> 00:29:46.640
you think about

00:29:46.640 --> 00:29:47.960
a discouraged individual.

00:29:47.960 --> 00:29:48.720
What you think about

00:29:48.720 --> 00:29:49.480
their countenance

00:29:49.480 --> 00:29:51.640
is that their their head is downward.

00:29:54.680 --> 00:29:56.960
But God is the lifter up of my head.

00:29:57.320 --> 00:29:59.360
He encourages us.

00:29:59.360 --> 00:30:00.280
What a joy that is.

00:30:00.280 --> 00:30:02.320
That is.

00:30:02.320 --> 00:30:05.600
And once we cast our burden unto the Lord,

00:30:05.600 --> 00:30:07.960
knowing that He will sustain us,

00:30:07.960 --> 00:30:09.840
we need to leave it with Him

00:30:09.840 --> 00:30:11.960
and just rest in God.

00:30:11.960 --> 00:30:13.360
Knowing that God is able.

00:30:13.360 --> 00:30:15.400
Be careful for nothing.

00:30:15.400 --> 00:30:18.280
Knowing that He is able to do in that situation

00:30:18.280 --> 00:30:19.680
what I cannot do,

00:30:19.680 --> 00:30:21.600
what you cannot do.

00:30:21.600 --> 00:30:25.080
And He's able to make it good.

00:30:25.080 --> 00:30:28.360
He's able to bring out of that situation

00:30:28.360 --> 00:30:32.320
something far greater than we could ever bring out of that situation.

00:30:32.320 --> 00:30:35.280
And we know that all things work together for good, right?

00:30:35.280 --> 00:30:37.120
Romans 8 and verse number 28.

00:30:37.120 --> 00:30:38.600
He wants us to know that.

00:30:38.600 --> 00:30:41.800
He wants us to have confidence in that.

00:30:41.800 --> 00:30:44.400
You know, that God would help us to rejoice.

00:30:44.400 --> 00:30:47.760
In the midst of difficulties? Absolutely.

00:30:47.760 --> 00:30:49.040
Because He says,

00:30:49.040 --> 00:30:51.240
this is the day the Lord hath made.

00:30:51.240 --> 00:30:53.760
I will rejoice and be glad in it.

00:30:53.760 --> 00:30:55.880
Rejoice in the Lord always.

00:30:55.880 --> 00:30:57.920
And again, I say rejoice.

00:30:57.960 --> 00:31:00.320
Rejoice evermore.

00:31:00.320 --> 00:31:03.880
There's really no wiggle room in the Scriptures

00:31:03.880 --> 00:31:04.880
to say, you know what?

00:31:04.880 --> 00:31:08.720
I deserve to be able to complain about this situation.

00:31:08.720 --> 00:31:11.560
You're not going to find any wiggle room in the Word of God.

00:31:11.560 --> 00:31:14.200
He says rejoice.

00:31:14.200 --> 00:31:17.120
And when we know who our God is,

00:31:17.120 --> 00:31:19.600
and when we know what He's able to do,

00:31:19.600 --> 00:31:22.160
it'll lead us to rejoicing.

00:31:22.160 --> 00:31:25.920
Oh, that God would help us to rejoice

00:31:25.920 --> 00:31:29.280
even in the midst of great difficulty.

00:31:29.280 --> 00:31:32.280
Father, we love You and we thank You for loving us.

00:31:32.280 --> 00:31:36.880
We thank You for this short psalm.

00:31:36.880 --> 00:31:39.600
That's been an encouragement to me.

00:31:39.600 --> 00:31:43.840
I trust a help to those that have had the opportunity

00:31:43.840 --> 00:31:49.480
to hear the teaching of Your Word.

00:31:49.480 --> 00:31:51.880
God, I know that each one of us

00:31:51.880 --> 00:31:57.640
deal with a variety of difficulties.

00:31:57.640 --> 00:32:02.040
And I know that sometimes those difficulties

00:32:02.040 --> 00:32:06.040
can be greater than at other times.

00:32:06.040 --> 00:32:09.120
But God, we rejoice in knowing that You're greater.

00:32:09.120 --> 00:32:10.640
That You have a plan and a purpose.

00:32:10.640 --> 00:32:16.160
And though we may not always understand it,

00:32:16.160 --> 00:32:21.680
it is important that we rest in that fact, that truth.

00:32:21.680 --> 00:32:24.040
God, would You help us to have confidence in who You are

00:32:24.040 --> 00:32:25.040
and what You're able to do?

00:32:25.040 --> 00:32:31.680
Would You help us to depend upon You wholly, fully, completely?

00:32:31.680 --> 00:32:37.680
Would You help us to rejoice, to rejoice greatly?

00:32:37.680 --> 00:32:39.000
Thank You for the privilege of prayer.

00:32:39.000 --> 00:32:41.280
I pray that You'd bless our time.

00:32:41.280 --> 00:32:42.520
We'll thank You for what You'll do.

00:32:42.520 --> 00:32:45.880
For it's in Christ's name we pray, amen.

